font.span: The labels in each node are the "network name" value of the node.
Functional standin for a routers' BGP ASN and all networks that it originates

ul.li: Perimeter color of nodes denotes the symmetric perimeter zone (SP-zone) value of the node
Red perimeters on nodes denote SP-zone 0.0 ("transit")
Brown perimeters on nodes denote SP-zone 0.0.1 ("workload")
Blue perimeters on nodes denote SP-zone 0.0.2("workload")
Green perimeters on nodes denote SP-zone 0.0.3("workload")
Nodes' line-type denotes the "symmetric-perimeter-node" (SPN) value of the node
Solid lines on nodes denote an SPN value of 0/"no"
Dotted lines on nodes denote an SPN value of 1/"yes"
thick(6px) edges denote at least one attached node has an integral path depth (IPD) of 0

li.span: denote that both attached nodes have an IPD of 1
Line-color of edges denotes the "shallowest" path affinity group (PAG) value of the nodes connected to the edge

b.font: PAG value: 0.1 (root of actual PAG hierarchy
